cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MS, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a computerized approach to quantitatively evaluate both appearance distinctions and 3D surface variations of lung nodules for lung cancer diagnosis. The method involves using deep convolutional neural networks for appearance feature extraction and a random forest classifier for malignancy estimation. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Medical Imaging (cs.MS), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
